                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1436: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Feely</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-17T10:00:00-03:32"
                            >October 17 [<hi rend="italic">18?</hi>], 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 18—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. The reply of the Bolivian Government to the neutrals’ notes of October
                        4th<note n="99" xml:id="d631fn99">See telegrams No. 56, October 3, noon, and
                        No. 57, October 3, 1 p.m., to the Minister in Bolivia, <ref target="#pg_757"
                            >p. 757</ref>.</note> was received at 10 p.m. last night and is
                    published in the local papers today. Bolivia accepts the suggestion that the
                    conference begin on November 11th. Finot will probably leave here October 30th
                    and arrive in Washington about November 17th. Text of note follows.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d631fn1">See telegram No. 128, October 18, 4 p.m., <hi rend="italic"
                            >infra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Feely</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
